# Interactive 3D Globe & Horizontal Timeline

The goal is to provide a premium storytelling experience where users "travel" across the globe as they scroll through Enicar's history (1956-1971).

## 1. 3D Globe (Interactive Earth)
- **Library:** `@react-three/fiber`, `@react-three/drei`.
- **Textures:** Night Earth texture with glowing city lights (as seen in the user's 3rd image).
- **Markers:** Discrete glowing points for Himalaya, London, USA, Japan, etc.
- **Auto-Rotation:** The globe will rotate based on the active year in the timeline.

## 2. Horizontal Scrolling (GSAP)
- **Pinning:** The entire [Timeline](file:///c:/Users/NGUYEN-DINHKIET/Documents/ReactJsProjects/enicar-chronicle/src/components/Timeline.tsx#39-272) section pins when it reaches the top of the viewport.
- **Horizontal Translation:** The timeline content (years and stories) scrolls sideways.
- **Globe Position:** The globe stays fixed (either in the background or at one side) while the timeline content passes around it.

